Python<pre><code>normalize_path(p: Union[str, Path]) -&gt; str
</code></pre> <p>Return a normalized absolute path string for stable testing/logging.</p> <p>Ensures platform-appropriate formatting and avoids returning Path objects so that tests can compare against stringified call arguments consistently.</p> Source code in <code>tenets/cli/commands/_utils.py</code> Python<pre><code>def normalize_path(p: Union[str, Path]) -&gt; str:
    """Return a normalized absolute path string for stable testing/logging.

    Ensures platform-appropriate formatting and avoids returning Path objects
    so that tests can compare against stringified call arguments consistently.
    """
    try:
        return str(Path(p).resolve())
    except Exception:
        return str(p)
